# Work Day Scheduler

## Description

The Work Day Scheduler is a simple, yet effective calendar app designed for scheduling your work day. It allows you to add, save, and view events for standard business hours (9 AM to 5 PM). Built with HTML, CSS (Bootstrap), JavaScript (jQuery), and Day.js, this application is user-friendly and responsive, making it suitable for both desktop and mobile use.

## Features

- **Current Day Display**: Shows the current day at the top of the calendar.
- **Time Blocks**: Provides time blocks for each hour of the standard business day (9 AM to 5 PM).
- **Color-Coded Time Blocks**: Each time block is color-coded to indicate whether it is in the past (gray), present (red), or future (green), based on the current hour.
- **Event Entry**: Allows users to click into a time block to enter an event.
- **Save Functionality**: Includes a save button for each time block to save the event text to local storage.
- **Persistent Data**: Events are saved in local storage, ensuring that they persist even when the page is refreshed.

## Usage

To use the Work Day Scheduler, simply:

1. Open the [planner](./Assets/planner-photo1.png) in your web browser.
2. Click into the time block for the current hour or any future hour.
3. [Enter](./Assets/planner-photo2.png) the event or task you wish to schedule.
4. Click the save button on the right side of the time block to save your event.
5. Refresh the page at any time to see that your events persist.

## Installation

No installation is required. You can access the Work Day Scheduler directly through your web browser.

## Technologies Used

